    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2: Immunofluorescence micrograph of SGII, Aβ, and DβH in the prefrontal cortex. SGII (red), Aβ (blue), and DβH(green) were labelled separately and marked by arrowheads. Magenta indicates co-localization between Aβ with canonical DCV marker SgII, and are marked by a thick arrow.\n\nFigure 3: Immunoperoxidase-DβH and dual immunogold-silver labelling (large and small gold-silver particles, for Aβ and SGII, respectively) were localized in the same tissue section. Gold-silver labelling for Aβ and SGII were readily distinguishable from each other and were localized to the appropriate cellular structures. Aβ (marked by arrowheads) was identified by large-sized gold-silver particles (>50 nm cross-sectional diameter; average 65nm) while SGII was labelled (marked by arrows) using small-sized gold-silver particles (<40 nm cross-sectional diameter; average 31 nm).\n\nNote: The paper does not comment on specificity and cross-reactivity of Aβ or SGII antibodies.. Experimental description: The paper does not mention any details on the species used, just mentions that the micrography results were performed on the infralimbic medial prefrontal cortex of naïve rats.",
